DNA M 1 CCTATCAATGATAGA
DNA N 1 TCTATCATTGATAGG

readAtStage 2
alignmentForces forceConstant 300
alignmentForces A     4       155     B       4       155
alignmentForces A     156     198     B       169     211
# It's good to offset the target a big so it is not initially superimposed on the template. This will make the initial rendering easier:
initialDisplacement B 4.0 0 0 

#threading A	4	155	B	4	155 300.0
#threading A	156	198	B	169	211 300.0

mobilizer Rigid A 4	 198
#mobilizer Rigid B 4	 203
mobilizer Rigid B 4	 22
mobilizer Rigid B 30	 34
mobilizer Rigid B 50   155
mobilizer Rigid B 169  211
mobilizer Rigid M 1	 15
mobilizer Rigid N 1	 15

constrainToGround A 4
constrainToGround M 1
constrainToGround N 1
readBlockEnd

readAtStage 3
# At the end of stage 2, the target is superimposed on the template. There are a couple of ways to get rid of the template, as we do in this stage.
# The first way to do it is to get the template chain out of the way:
initialDisplacement A 10 0 0
reportingInterval .001
numReportingIntervals 1
mobilizer Rigid

readBlockEnd


